# Instagram feed (optional) — powers the "Our Instagram" gallery.
#
# Without these, the gallery falls back to the curated images in consts.ts.
# With a token, the build pulls the latest posts from @mariostintshop via the
# Instagram Graph API (refreshes on each deploy — rebuild to fetch new posts).
#
# How to get a long-lived token:
#   1. Convert @mariostintshop to a Professional (Business/Creator) account.
#   2. Create a Meta app → add "Instagram" → Instagram API with Instagram Login.
#   3. Generate a User access token, then exchange it for a long-lived token
#      (~60 days, refreshable) with the ig_user_media scope.
# Paste the long-lived token below (copy this file to `.env`).

INSTAGRAM_TOKEN=
# Optional; defaults to "me" (the token's own account).
INSTAGRAM_USER_ID=
